Tuesday, February 16, 1999 
The Senate met at 2:00 p.m., the Speaker in the Chair.  
The Hon. the Speaker :
On behalf of all honourable senators, I welcome you to the Senate of Canada.  
New Year is celebrated according to the Chinese lunar calendar. 
Today, the Year of the Rabbit begins.  
Children and unmarried friends are given "lai see" by those who are married. 
Those little red envelopes have money inside for good fortune.  
Eating these foods bestows their wishes on those who consume them. 
